description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an Assistant Psychologist to join our Devon wide Learning Disability Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with our Learning Disability Nurses and colleagues in Health, Social Care &amp; Education you’ll support the Clinical Psychologists in the team with psychological assessment, interventions and also support our service development by playing a key role in our audit and evaluation processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will support Children and Young People with a Learning Disability and their families in the way that you believe is best, delivering our high service standards, sharing best practice, and actively improving the way we work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be a Psychology Graduate, with previous experience of working either with Children &amp; Young People or in a Learning Disability setting and with strong communication and organisation skills, and a flexible approach will ensure you deliver positive experiences to Children and Young People with a Learning Disability at every stage of their healthcare journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
